%N A396725 Fill the square spiral the greedy way with distinct nonnegative integers such that not two points of the form (x, y, z) where 2^z appears in the binary expansion of the value at cell (x, y) are a knight's move apart.
%C A396725 A 3-dimensional variant of A394166 and A396603.
%C A396725 Two points (x, y, z) and (x', y', z') are a knight's move apart iff {abs(x-x'), abs(y-y'), abs(z-z')} = {0, 1, 2}.
%C A396725 For any k >= 0, the first term >= 2^k is a power of 2.
%H A396725 Rémy Sigrist, <a href="/A396725/b396725.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..10200</a>
